            . I am a Police-officer. On the 1st of July, within a few minutes of nine o'clock at night, I was near Hackney church-tower; the prisoner passed me, and had nothing with him - in about two minutes he passed me again, with something concealed under his coat; on going to see what it was, I found this straw hat, which he said. he had bought in a public-house, at Clapton, for 6d.: I looked in it, saw Mr. Merry's name, and went there - he was about one hundred yards from the prosecutor's.</p>
               <p>CHRISTIANA BURGESS. I lived with Mr. Merry - he <rs id="t18310908-203-viclabel1050" type="occupation">keeps a straw-hat warehouse</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-203-victim1533 t18310908-203-viclabel1050"></join>. This hat is his; it had been taken from the end of the counter, near the door - I had seen it a few minutes before eight o'clock.</p>
